Spherical Pole is a easy spot for artifact to occur, because the default sphere mesh has a high valence vertex(star), a vertice with many edges connecting to it. 

Like this. 

![](data:image/png;base64,)

To fix this, we first need to use multi-cut tool to add edges. 

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Then, we delete some original edges but keep the center ones since the original geo has that y-axis info we do not have with these new adding edges. Without that, we would have a completely flat surface at the pole. 

![](data:image/png;base64,)

![](data:image/png;base64,)

This method greatly reduces the impact of this pole artifact but cannot completely erase it.  

Another way to do is to use a eight-side sphere with the pole triangles turned into quads, then smooth it. But if we have to have more subdivision geo, then the above method is our best bet. 

![](data:image/png;base64,)
